Create the KDSrootkey:
Add-KdsRootKey -EffectiveTime ((Get-Date).AddHours(-10))
Create gmsa account:
New-ADServiceAccount -Name gMsa -Description "gMsa for cluster" 
-DNSHostName servFAB.fabrikam.com 
-PrincipalsAllowedToRetrieveManagedPassword cluster 
-Enabled $True

This the permission might be denied, you need to set the permissionrunning this:
Set-ADServiceAccount gMsa -PrincipalsAllowedToRetrieveManagedPassword "CN=cluster,CN=Computers,DC=fabrikam,DC=com"




2nd gmsa
New-ADServiceAccount -Name gMsa2 -Description "gMsa for cluster" -DNSHostName WIN1FAB0.fabrikam.com -PrincipalsAllowedToRetrieveManagedPassword WIN1FAB0$ -Enabled $True

Verify gmsa:
Get-ADServiceAccount gMsa

Install gmsa on the machine you want to use it for:
Install-ADServiceAccount -Identity gMsa2

Test-ADServiceAccount gMsa2
Uninstall-ADServiceAccount gMsa2
Remove-ADServiceAccount -Identity gMsa2

